  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/items/weapons/ratfolk-tail-blade.png",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>A tailblade is a small, sharp knife designed to be strapped to the tip of a wielder’s tail.</em></p>\n<p>A ratfolk wielding a tailblade can make a tail attack, adding its&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/cleric/domains/paizo-domains/strength-domain\">Strength</a>&nbsp;modifier to the tailblade’s damage.</p>\n<p>Ratfolk are considered proficient with such attacks and can apply feats or effects appropriate to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Natural-Attacks\">natural attacks</a>&nbsp;to tail attacks made with a tailblade. If used as part of a full attack action, attacks with a tailblade are considered secondary attacks.</p>\n<p>It takes a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Full-Round-Actions\">full-round action</a>&nbsp;to strap on or remove a tailblade. The wearer can loosely attach the tailblade (without strapping it securely in place) as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Move-Actions\">move action</a>, but using a loosely attached tailblade gives the wielder a –4 penalty on all&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Roll\">attack rolls</a>&nbsp;made with the weapon, and other creatures get a +4 bonus on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Disarm\">disarm</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Combat-Maneuvers\">combat maneuver</a>&nbsp;checks to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Disarm\">disarm</a>&nbsp;the tailblade.</p>"
    },
